Breakfast was plentiful with a variety of rolls, juices, fruit, cheese etc and hot coffee or tea.	Breakfast was served in a small dining room but there was a good choice of cold meats, bread rolls and pastries, yoghurt and limited fresh fruit (but it was March).	The breakfast was very nice with a large selection of yogurts, breads, cheeses, and fresh fruits.	The breakfast next morning was very good, a lovely cosy and well decorated breakfast room and a great choice at the buffet.	The breakfast was also relatively good compared to other hotels in Italy, and provide an option for freshly prepared food, eggs etc, although there is an additional cost.